### [2 Chronicles Chapter 7](../../../bib/kjv/ch2007.htm#001.md)

[2 Chronicles](../../../bib/kjv/ch2001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">ch2 7:0</span></span>

Overview

[Ch2 7:1](../../../bib/kjv/ch2007.htm#001.md), God having given testimony
to Solomon's prayer by fire from heaven, and glory in the temple, the
people worship him; [Ch2 7:4](../../../bib/kjv/ch2007.htm#004.md),
Solomon's solemn sacrifice; [Ch2 7:8](../../../bib/kjv/ch2007.htm#008.md),
Solomon having kept the feast of tabernacles, and the feast of
dedication of the altar, dismisses the people; [Ch2
7:12](../../../bib/kjv/ch2007.htm#012.md), God appearing to Solomon, gives
him promises upon condition.

